<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1476" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1476">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/95.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Edwards</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Juarez</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-19">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s February 19. This Consul visited General Villa in his
                                private office this afternoon and informed him of instructions of
                                Honorable Secretary of State Bryan, at the request of British
                                Ambassador. General Villa stated that he was anxious that my
                                Government and the British Government should know the facts with
                                reference to William Benton and that he is dead. That Benton came to
                                his house armed and attempted to kill him. Villa produced large
                                pistol which he said Benton brought with him. I will convey the
                                facts to the family and send full particulars to the Department by
                                next mail.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>